{"descriptions":[{"id":1279,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe forms \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདི་འདྲས་\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདི་འདྲས་ཟེ་\u003c/span\u003e may both be translated by \u0026ldquo;like this\u0026rdquo; or \u0026ldquo;thus.\u0026rdquo; They differ in the same way as the interrogatives \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eག་འདྲས་\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eག་འདྲས་ཟེ་\u003c/span\u003e. (xxlink 30.3.3) The form \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདུག་ཟེ་\u003c/span\u003e is sometimes used instead of \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདི་འདྲས་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐྲ་སུ་ལུ་འདི་འདྲས་སྙིང་རྗེ་པོ་རེད་བ།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Curly hair like that is nice, isn\u0026rsquo;t it?\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདུག་ཟེ་རྒྱག་དགོས་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;It should be done like this.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁོང་གིས་ཡི་གེ་འདི་འདྲས་ཟེ་འབྲི་གི་འདུག\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;He writes like this.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:25 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:25 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}